### 3.2 Total Risk with Zero Correlation
- **Calculation**:
  - Assuming zero correlation among [risk factors](../../Financial%20Instruments/Assignments/PSET%206-%20Financial%20Instruments.md),  total risk = \( \sqrt{11.3^2 + 6.9^2 + 3.2^2 + 2.9^2 + 0.2^2} = 13.9 \,  \text{bp/month} \).
- **Insights**:
  - This scenario is unrealistic,  as [risk factors](../../Financial%20Instruments/Assignments/PSET%206-%20Financial%20Instruments.md) are typically correlated.
  - Correlations must be incorporated to understand the true risk profile.

