## **4. Summary and Key Takeaways**

### **4.1 Eurodollar Futures**
- [Eurodollar futures](../../Financial%20Markets/Financial%20Engineering%20and%20Arbitrage%20in%20the%20Financial%20Markets/PART%20I%20RELATIVE%20VALUE%20BUILDING%20BLOCKS/Chapter%206%20Options%20on%20Non-Price%20Variables/Convexity-Adjusted%20Models%20for%20LIBOR%20Forwards%20Qu.md) are widely used for [hedging](../../Financial%20Markets/Fixed%20Income%20Securities%20Tools%20for%20Today's%20Markets/Chapter%205/Key%20Rates%20O1s%20Durations%20and%20Hedging.md) and speculating on short-term [interest rates](../../Financial%20Markets/Fixed%20Income%20Securities%20Tools%20for%20Today's%20Markets/Chapter%202/Interest%20Rate%20Quotations.md).
- The transition from [Basis Swap](A%20Guide%20to%20the%20Front%20End%20and%20[[Basis%20Swaps) Markets#[London Interbank Offered Rate](../../Financial%20Markets/Fixed%20Income%20Securities%20Tools%20for%20Today's%20Markets/Chapter%2012/Short-Term%20Rates%20and%20the%20Transition%20from%20LIBOR.md) (LIBOR)|LIBOR]] to SOFR represents a significant shift in the [short-term interest rate](../../Financial%20Markets/Fixed%20Income%20Securities%20Tools%20for%20Today's%20Markets/Chapter%209/The%20Gauss%20Model.md) market.

### **4.2 Treasury Bill Futures**
- Treasury bill [futures](../../Financial%20Markets/Financial%20Engineering%20and%20Arbitrage%20in%20the%20Financial%20Markets/PART%20I%20RELATIVE%20VALUE%20BUILDING%20BLOCKS/Chapter%203%20-%20Futures%20Markets/Futures%20Not%20Subject%20to%20Cash-And-Carry.md) provide a straightforward means of [hedging](../../Financial%20Markets/Fixed%20Income%20Securities%20Tools%20for%20Today's%20Markets/Chapter%205/Key%20Rates%20O1s%20Durations%20and%20Hedging.md) or speculating on the short end of the yield curve.
- Their simplicity and [liquidity](../../Financial%20Markets%20and%20Institutions/III.%20Liquidity%20of%20Assets/Class%205-%20Private%20Information,%20Liquidity,%20and%20Securitization/Class%20Note%2010%20Liquidity%20and%20Class%20Note%2010%20Liquidity%20and%20Liquidity%20Managementliquidity%20management.md) make them a popular choice for market participants.

### **4.3 Practical Applications**
- Both Eurodollar and Treasury bill [futures](../../Financial%20Markets/Financial%20Engineering%20and%20Arbitrage%20in%20the%20Financial%20Markets/PART%20I%20RELATIVE%20VALUE%20BUILDING%20BLOCKS/Chapter%203%20-%20Futures%20Markets/Futures%20Not%20Subject%20to%20Cash-And-Carry.md) are essential tools for [managing interest rate risk](Lecture%20Notes%204-Mechanics%20of%20Futures%20Trading%20and%20Fixed%20Income%20Derivatives.md) and optimizing [portfolio](../../Advanced%20Investments/An%20Asset%20Allocation%20Primer.md) performance.
- Understanding the [pricing](../../Financial%20Markets/Fixed%20Income%20Securities%20Tools%20for%20Today's%20Markets/Chapter%207/Arbitrage%20Pricing%20of%20Derivatives.md) conventions and applications of these contracts is critical for effective [risk management](../../Financial%20Engineering/Financial%20Mathematics%20Course.md).

By leveraging these instruments,  [portfolio](../../Advanced%20Investments/An%20Asset%20Allocation%20Primer.md) managers can navigate the complexities of [short-term interest rate](../../Financial%20Markets/Fixed%20Income%20Securities%20Tools%20for%20Today's%20Markets/Chapter%209/The%20Gauss%20Model.md) markets and achieve their [investment](../../Advanced%20Investments/An%20Asset%20Allocation%20Primer.md) objectives.

This concludes the lecture notes on [Eurodollar futures](../../Financial%20Markets/Financial%20Engineering%20and%20Arbitrage%20in%20the%20Financial%20Markets/PART%20I%20RELATIVE%20VALUE%20BUILDING%20BLOCKS/Chapter%206%20Options%20on%20Non-Price%20Variables/Convexity-Adjusted%20Models%20for%20LIBOR%20Forwards%20Qu.md),  Treasury bill [futures](../../Financial%20Markets/Financial%20Engineering%20and%20Arbitrage%20in%20the%20Financial%20Markets/PART%20I%20RELATIVE%20VALUE%20BUILDING%20BLOCKS/Chapter%203%20-%20Futures%20Markets/Futures%20Not%20Subject%20to%20Cash-And-Carry.md),  and their applications in [fixed income](../Lecture%20Notes%20Bonds,%20%20Preferred%20Stock,%20%20and%20Structured%20Products.md) [portfolio management](../../Financial%20Engineering/Fixed%20Income%20Derivatives/The%20Impact%20of%20Option%20Strategies%20in%20Financial%20%20Portfolios%20Performance.md). Next,  we will explore advanced techniques for integrating these instruments into [portfolio optimization](../../Financial%20Markets/Financial%20Engineering%20and%20Arbitrage%20in%20the%20Financial%20Markets/PART%20III%20THE%20PLAYERS/Chapter%2011%20-%20Individual%20Investors-A%20Survey%20of%20Modern%20Investment%20Theory/The%20Modern%20Portfolio%20Theory%20and%20the%20Capm.md) and [risk management](../../Financial%20Engineering/Financial%20Mathematics%20Course.md) frameworks.

### **Lecture Notes: Eurodollar Futures,  SOFR Futures,  [](../Fixed%20Income%20Lecture%20Notes/A%20Guide%20to%20the%20Front%20End%20and%20Basis%20Swap%20Markets.md#Federal%20Funds%20Market|Fed%20Funds) Futures,  and Advanced Interest Rate Futures Contracts**

## **1. Eurodollar Futures**

### **1.1 Overview**
- **Definition**: [Eurodollar futures](../../Financial%20Markets/Financial%20Engineering%20and%20Arbitrage%20in%20the%20Financial%20Markets/PART%20I%20RELATIVE%20VALUE%20BUILDING%20BLOCKS/Chapter%206%20Options%20on%20Non-Price%20Variables/Convexity-Adjusted%20Models%20for%20LIBOR%20Forwards%20Qu.md) are contracts based on the interest rate of U.S. dollar-denominated time deposits held in banks outside the United States.
- **Underlying Instrument**: Three-month [Basis Swap](A%20Guide%20to%20the%20Front%20End%20and%20[[Basis%20Swaps) Markets#[London Interbank Offered Rate](../../Financial%20Markets/Fixed%20Income%20Securities%20Tools%20for%20Today's%20Markets/Chapter%2012/Short-Term%20Rates%20and%20the%20Transition%20from%20LIBOR.md) (LIBOR)|LIBOR]] ([London Interbank Offered Rate](../../Financial%20Markets/Fixed%20Income%20Securities%20Tools%20for%20Today's%20Markets/Chapter%2012/Short-Term%20Rates%20and%20the%20Transition%20from%20LIBOR.md)).
- **Contract Size**: $1,  000,  000 face value.
- **Settlement**: Cash-settled based on the three-month [Basis Swap](A%20Guide%20to%20the%20Front%20End%20and%20[[Basis%20Swaps) Markets#[London Interbank Offered Rate](../../Financial%20Markets/Fixed%20Income%20Securities%20Tools%20for%20Today's%20Markets/Chapter%2012/Short-Term%20Rates%20and%20the%20Transition%20from%20LIBOR.md) (LIBOR)|LIBOR]] rate at contract expiration.

### **1.2 Pricing and Quotation**
- **Index Price Basis**:
  - [Futures price](../../Financial%20Markets/Fixed%20Income%20Securities%20Tools%20for%20Today's%20Markets/Chapter%2011/Futures%20Price%20and%20the%20Quality%20Option%20Before%20E.md) = \( 100 - \text{[Basis Swap](A%20Guide%20to%20the%20Front%20End%20and%20[[Basis%20Swaps) Markets#[London Interbank Offered Rate](../../Financial%20Markets/Fixed%20Income%20Securities%20Tools%20for%20Today's%20Markets/Chapter%2012/Short-Term%20Rates%20and%20the%20Transition%20from%20LIBOR.md) (LIBOR)|LIBOR]] rate} \).
  - Example: If [Basis Swap](A%20Guide%20to%20the%20Front%20End%20and%20[[Basis%20Swaps) Markets#[London Interbank Offered Rate](../../Financial%20Markets/Fixed%20Income%20Securities%20Tools%20for%20Today's%20Markets/Chapter%2012/Short-Term%20Rates%20and%20the%20Transition%20from%20LIBOR.md) (LIBOR)|LIBOR]] is 2.50%,  the [futures price](../../Financial%20Markets/Fixed%20Income%20Securities%20Tools%20for%20Today's%20Markets/Chapter%2011/Futures%20Price%20and%20the%20Quality%20Option%20Before%20E.md) is \( 100 - 2.50 = 97.50 \).
- **Tick Value**:
  - A 0.01% (1 basis point) change in the [Basis Swap](A%20Guide%20to%20the%20Front%20End%20and%20[[Basis%20Swaps) Markets#[London Interbank Offered Rate](../../Financial%20Markets/Fixed%20Income%20Securities%20Tools%20for%20Today's%20Markets/Chapter%2012/Short-Term%20Rates%20and%20the%20Transition%20from%20LIBOR.md) (LIBOR)|LIBOR]] rate results in a $25 change in the contract's value:
	$$ \Delta \text{Value} = \$1,  000,  000 \times 0.0001 \times \frac{90}{360} = \$25 $$
- **Minimum Tick Size**:
  - The minimum price fluctuation (tick) is 0.005 or ½ basis point,  with a tick value of $12.50:
	$$ \text{Tick Value} = \$1,  000,  000 \times (0.005 \times \frac{90}{360}) = \$12.50 $$

### **1.3 Example: Profit/Loss Calculation**
- **Scenario**:
  - An investor buys one [Eurodollar futures](../../Financial%20Markets/Financial%20Engineering%20and%20Arbitrage%20in%20the%20Financial%20Markets/PART%20I%20RELATIVE%20VALUE%20BUILDING%20BLOCKS/Chapter%206%20Options%20on%20Non-Price%20Variables/Convexity-Adjusted%20Models%20for%20LIBOR%20Forwards%20Qu.md) contract at a price of 98.00 (implying a [Basis Swap](A%20Guide%20to%20the%20Front%20End%20and%20[[Basis%20Swaps) Markets#[London Interbank Offered Rate](../../Financial%20Markets/Fixed%20Income%20Securities%20Tools%20for%20Today's%20Markets/Chapter%2012/Short-Term%20Rates%20and%20the%20Transition%20from%20LIBOR.md) (LIBOR)|LIBOR]] rate of 2.00%).
  - One week later,  the [Basis Swap](A%20Guide%20to%20the%20Front%20End%20and%20[[Basis%20Swaps) Markets#[London Interbank Offered Rate](../../Financial%20Markets/Fixed%20Income%20Securities%20Tools%20for%20Today's%20Markets/Chapter%2012/Short-Term%20Rates%20and%20the%20Transition%20from%20LIBOR.md) (LIBOR)|LIBOR]] rate increases by 20 basis points to 2.20%,  causing the [futures price](../../Financial%20Markets/Fixed%20Income%20Securities%20Tools%20for%20Today's%20Markets/Chapter%2011/Futures%20Price%20and%20the%20Quality%20Option%20Before%20E.md) to decline to 97.80.
- **Loss Calculation**:
  - Change in price = \( 98.00 - 97.80 = 0.20 \).
  - Loss = \( \$1,  000,  000 \times 0.20\% \times \frac{90}{360} = \$500 \).
  - Alternatively,  using tick value:
	- 20 basis points = \( 20 \times \$25 = -\$500 \).

### **1.4 Packs and Bundles**
- **Packs**:
  - Groups of four quarterly [Eurodollar futures](../../Financial%20Markets/Financial%20Engineering%20and%20Arbitrage%20in%20the%20Financial%20Markets/PART%20I%20RELATIVE%20VALUE%20BUILDING%20BLOCKS/Chapter%206%20Options%20on%20Non-Price%20Variables/Convexity-Adjusted%20Models%20for%20LIBOR%20Forwards%20Qu.md) contracts traded together.
  - Examples:
	- **White Pack**: First four quarterly contracts (e.g.,  Jun 20,  Sep 20,  Dec 20,  Mar 21).
	- **Red Pack**: Next four quarterly contracts (e.g.,  Jun 21,  Sep 21,  Dec 21,  Mar 22).
  - Value of 1 basis point = \( 4 \times \$25 = \$100 \).
- **Bundles**:
  - Groups of multiple packs traded together.
  - Examples:
	- **White Bundle**: First four contracts (\$100 per basis point).
	- **Red Bundle**: First eight contracts (\$200 per basis point).
	- **Green Bundle**: First 12 contracts (\$300 per basis point).
	- **Copper Bundle**: First 40 contracts (\$1,  000 per basis point).

### **1.5 Transition from [](../Fixed%20Income%20Lecture%20Notes/A%20Guide%20to%20the%20Front%20End%20and%20Basis%20Swap%20Markets.md#London%20Interbank%20Offered%20Rate%20(LIBOR)|LIBOR) to SOFR**
- **[Basis Swap](A%20Guide%20to%20the%20Front%20End%20and%20[[Basis%20Swaps) Markets#[London Interbank Offered Rate](../../Financial%20Markets/Fixed%20Income%20Securities%20Tools%20for%20Today's%20Markets/Chapter%2012/Short-Term%20Rates%20and%20the%20Transition%20from%20LIBOR.md) (LIBOR)|LIBOR]] Phase-Out**:
  - [Basis Swap](A%20Guide%20to%20the%20Front%20End%20and%20[[Basis%20Swaps) Markets#[London Interbank Offered Rate](../../Financial%20Markets/Fixed%20Income%20Securities%20Tools%20for%20Today's%20Markets/Chapter%2012/Short-Term%20Rates%20and%20the%20Transition%20from%20LIBOR.md) (LIBOR)|LIBOR]] will be replaced by SOFR ([Secured Overnight Financing Rate](../../Financial%20Markets/Fixed%20Income%20Securities%20Tools%20for%20Today's%20Markets/Chapter%2010/SOFR.md)) due to reliability concerns.
- **[SOFR Futures](../../Financial%20Markets/Fixed%20Income%20Securities%20Tools%20for%20Today's%20Markets/Chapter%2012/One-Month%20SOFR%20Futures.md)**:
  - Similar to [Eurodollar futures](../../Financial%20Markets/Financial%20Engineering%20and%20Arbitrage%20in%20the%20Financial%20Markets/PART%20I%20RELATIVE%20VALUE%20BUILDING%20BLOCKS/Chapter%206%20Options%20on%20Non-Price%20Variables/Convexity-Adjusted%20Models%20for%20LIBOR%20Forwards%20Qu.md) but based on compounded daily SOFR interest during the reference quarter.
  - Price = \( 100 - \text{SOFR rate} \).
  - Tick value = $25 per basis point.

## **2. SOFR Interest Rate Futures**

### **2.1 Overview**
- **Definition**: [Futures contracts](../../Financial%20Engineering/Mathematics%20of%20the%20Financial%20Markets.md) based on the [Secured Overnight Financing Rate](../../Financial%20Markets/Fixed%20Income%20Securities%20Tools%20for%20Today's%20Markets/Chapter%2010/SOFR.md) (SOFR),  a benchmark interest rate for [repurchase agreements](../../Financial%20Markets%20and%20Institutions/III.%20Liquidity%20of%20Assets/Class%207-%20CP,%20Repo,%20and%20the%20Crisis/Class%20Slides%20On%20Repurchase%20Agreements.md).
- **Underlying Instrument**: Compounded daily SOFR interest during the reference quarter.
- **Contract Size**: $1,  000,  000 face value.
- **Settlement**: Cash-settled.

### **2.2 Pricing and Quotation**
- **Index Price Basis**:
  - [Futures price](../../Financial%20Markets/Fixed%20Income%20Securities%20Tools%20for%20Today's%20Markets/Chapter%2011/Futures%20Price%20and%20the%20Quality%20Option%20Before%20E.md) = \( 100 - \text{SOFR rate} \).
- **Tick Value**:
  - A 1 basis point change in the SOFR rate results in a $25 change in the contract's value.

## **3. [](../Fixed%20Income%20Lecture%20Notes/A%20Guide%20to%20the%20Front%20End%20and%20Basis%20Swap%20Markets.md#Federal%20Funds%20Market|Fed%20Funds) Futures**

### **3.1 Overview**
- **Definition**: [Futures contracts](../../Financial%20Engineering/Mathematics%20of%20the%20Financial%20Markets.md) based on the average overnight [federal funds rate](../../International%20Finance/Economic%20Stabilization%20Notes/Topics%20in%20Fiscal%20and%20Monetary%20Policies%20and%20Stabilization-%20Empirical%20Issues.md) for the [delivery month](../../Financial%20Markets/Fixed%20Income%20Securities%20Tools%20for%20Today's%20Markets/Chapter%2012/One-Month%20SOFR%20Futures.md).
- **Underlying Instrument**: Simple average overnight [federal funds rate](../../International%20Finance/Economic%20Stabilization%20Notes/Topics%20in%20Fiscal%20and%20Monetary%20Policies%20and%20Stabilization-%20Empirical%20Issues.md).
- **Contract Size**: $5,  000,  000 notional value.
- **Settlement**: Cash-settled on the last business day of the month.

### **3.2 Pricing and Quotation**
- **Index Price Basis**:
  - [Futures price](../../Financial%20Markets/Fixed%20Income%20Securities%20Tools%20for%20Today's%20Markets/Chapter%2011/Futures%20Price%20and%20the%20Quality%20Option%20Before%20E.md) = \( 100 - \text{[Basis Swap](A%20Guide%20to%20the%20Front%20End%20and%20[[Basis%20Swaps) Markets#Federal Funds Market|[Fed Funds](../../Financial%20Markets/Fixed%20Income%20Securities%20Tools%20for%20Today's%20Markets/Chapter%2012/Fed%20Fund%20Futures.md) Rate]] } \).
- **Tick Value**:
  - A 1 basis point change in the [Basis Swap](A%20Guide%20to%20the%20Front%20End%20and%20[[Basis%20Swaps) Markets#Federal Funds Market|[Fed Funds](../../Financial%20Markets/Fixed%20Income%20Securities%20Tools%20for%20Today's%20Markets/Chapter%2012/Fed%20Fund%20Futures.md) Rate]]  results in a $41.67 change in the contract's value:
	$$ \Delta \text{Value} = \$5,  000,  000 \times 0.0001 \times \frac{30}{360} = \$41.67 $$

## **4. Swap Futures Contracts**

### **4.1 Overview**
- **Definition**: [Futures contracts](../../Financial%20Engineering/Mathematics%20of%20the%20Financial%20Markets.md) based on the notional price of the fixed-rate side of a 10-year [interest rate swap](../../Financial%20Engineering/Primer%20on%20Interest%20Rate%20Swaps.md).
- **Underlying Instrument**: 10-year [interest rate swap](../../Financial%20Engineering/Primer%20on%20Interest%20Rate%20Swaps.md) with a [notional principal](../../Financial%20Markets/Financial%20Engineering%20and%20Arbitrage%20in%20the%20Financial%20Markets/PART%20I%20RELATIVE%20VALUE%20BUILDING%20BLOCKS/Chapter%204%20-%20Swap%20Markets/Fundamentals%20of%20Swaps.md) of $100,  000.
- **Settlement**: Cash-settled based on the ISDA benchmark 10-year [swap rate](../Fixed%20Income%20Lecture%20Notes/Teaching%20Note%204%20Interest%20Rate%20Derivatives.md).

### **4.2 Applications**
- **[Hedging](../../Financial%20Markets/Fixed%20Income%20Securities%20Tools%20for%20Today's%20Markets/Chapter%205/Key%20Rates%20O1s%20Durations%20and%20Hedging.md)**:
  - Used to hedge [interest rate risk](../Analysis%20of%20Fixed%20Income%20Securities.md) in swap portfolios.
- **Speculation**:
  - Traders can speculate on changes in swap rates.

## **5. Other Futures Contracts**

### **5.1 Treasury Futures**
- **On-the-Run (OTR) Treasury [Futures](../../Financial%20Markets/Financial%20Engineering%20and%20Arbitrage%20in%20the%20Financial%20Markets/PART%20I%20RELATIVE%20VALUE%20BUILDING%20BLOCKS/Chapter%203%20-%20Futures%20Markets/Futures%20Not%20Subject%20to%20Cash-And-Carry.md)**:
  - Based on the most recently auctioned 2-year,  5-year,  and 10-year Treasury notes.
  - Cash-settled with a notional value of $100,  000.

### **5.2 Credit Futures**
- **Barclays U.S. Aggregate Bond Index [Futures](../../Financial%20Markets/Financial%20Engineering%20and%20Arbitrage%20in%20the%20Financial%20Markets/PART%20I%20RELATIVE%20VALUE%20BUILDING%20BLOCKS/Chapter%203%20-%20Futures%20Markets/Futures%20Not%20Subject%20to%20Cash-And-Carry.md)**:
  - Based on the Barclays Capital U.S. Aggregate Bond Index.
  - Includes Treasury,  agency,  corporate,  mortgage-backed,  [asset-backed](../../Financial%20Markets%20and%20Institutions/III.%20Liquidity%20of%20Assets/Class%207-%20CP,%20Repo,%20and%20the%20Crisis/Asset%20Backed%20Commercial%20Paper%20Understanding%20the%20Risks.md),  and commercial [mortgage-backed securities](../../Financial%20Markets%20and%20Institutions/III.%20Liquidity%20of%20Assets/Class%207-%20CP,%20Repo,%20and%20the%20Crisis/Fremont%20Financial%20Corp.%20(b).md).

## **6. Summary and Key Takeaways**

### **6.1 Eurodollar Futures**
- [Eurodollar futures](../../Financial%20Markets/Financial%20Engineering%20and%20Arbitrage%20in%20the%20Financial%20Markets/PART%20I%20RELATIVE%20VALUE%20BUILDING%20BLOCKS/Chapter%206%20Options%20on%20Non-Price%20Variables/Convexity-Adjusted%20Models%20for%20LIBOR%20Forwards%20Qu.md) are widely used for [hedging](../../Financial%20Markets/Fixed%20Income%20Securities%20Tools%20for%20Today's%20Markets/Chapter%205/Key%20Rates%20O1s%20Durations%20and%20Hedging.md) and speculating on short-term [interest rates](../../Financial%20Markets/Fixed%20Income%20Securities%20Tools%20for%20Today's%20Markets/Chapter%202/Interest%20Rate%20Quotations.md).
- Packs and bundles provide exposure to different segments of the yield curve.

### **6.2 SOFR Futures**
- [SOFR futures](../../Financial%20Markets/Fixed%20Income%20Securities%20Tools%20for%20Today's%20Markets/Chapter%2012/One-Month%20SOFR%20Futures.md) are the successor to [Eurodollar futures](../../Financial%20Markets/Financial%20Engineering%20and%20Arbitrage%20in%20the%20Financial%20Markets/PART%20I%20RELATIVE%20VALUE%20BUILDING%20BLOCKS/Chapter%206%20Options%20on%20Non-Price%20Variables/Convexity-Adjusted%20Models%20for%20LIBOR%20Forwards%20Qu.md),  reflecting the transition from [Basis Swap](A%20Guide%20to%20the%20Front%20End%20and%20[[Basis%20Swaps) Markets#[London Interbank Offered Rate](../../Financial%20Markets/Fixed%20Income%20Securities%20Tools%20for%20Today's%20Markets/Chapter%2012/Short-Term%20Rates%20and%20the%20Transition%20from%20LIBOR.md) (LIBOR)|LIBOR]] to SOFR.

### **6.3 [](../Fixed%20Income%20Lecture%20Notes/A%20Guide%20to%20the%20Front%20End%20and%20Basis%20Swap%20Markets.md#Federal%20Funds%20Market|Fed%20Funds) Futures**
- [Basis Swap](A%20Guide%20to%20the%20Front%20End%20and%20[[Basis%20Swaps) Markets#Federal Funds Market|[Fed Funds](../../Financial%20Markets/Fixed%20Income%20Securities%20Tools%20for%20Today's%20Markets/Chapter%2012/Fed%20Fund%20Futures.md)]] [futures](../../Financial%20Markets/Financial%20Engineering%20and%20Arbitrage%20in%20the%20Financial%20Markets/PART%20I%20RELATIVE%20VALUE%20BUILDING%20BLOCKS/Chapter%203%20-%20Futures%20Markets/Futures%20Not%20Subject%20to%20Cash-And-Carry.md) allow market participants to hedge or speculate on changes in the [federal funds rate](../../International%20Finance/Economic%20Stabilization%20Notes/Topics%20in%20Fiscal%20and%20Monetary%20Policies%20and%20Stabilization-%20Empirical%20Issues.md).

### **6.4 Swap Futures**
- Swap [futures](../../Financial%20Markets/Financial%20Engineering%20and%20Arbitrage%20in%20the%20Financial%20Markets/PART%20I%20RELATIVE%20VALUE%20BUILDING%20BLOCKS/Chapter%203%20-%20Futures%20Markets/Futures%20Not%20Subject%20to%20Cash-And-Carry.md) provide exposure to interest rate swaps and are [used for hedging and speculation](../../Clippings/Options%20Contract%20-%20Types%20of%20Contracts.md).

### **6.5 Treasury and Credit Futures**
- Treasury [futures](../../Financial%20Markets/Financial%20Engineering%20and%20Arbitrage%20in%20the%20Financial%20Markets/PART%20I%20RELATIVE%20VALUE%20BUILDING%20BLOCKS/Chapter%203%20-%20Futures%20Markets/Futures%20Not%20Subject%20to%20Cash-And-Carry.md) provide synthetic exposure to benchmark maturities on the U.S. Treasury yield curve.
- Credit [futures](../../Financial%20Markets/Financial%20Engineering%20and%20Arbitrage%20in%20the%20Financial%20Markets/PART%20I%20RELATIVE%20VALUE%20BUILDING%20BLOCKS/Chapter%203%20-%20Futures%20Markets/Futures%20Not%20Subject%20to%20Cash-And-Carry.md) allow for [hedging](../../Financial%20Markets/Fixed%20Income%20Securities%20Tools%20for%20Today's%20Markets/Chapter%205/Key%20Rates%20O1s%20Durations%20and%20Hedging.md) and speculation on credit spreads and bond market performance.

By understanding these instruments,  [portfolio](../../Advanced%20Investments/An%20Asset%20Allocation%20Primer.md) managers can effectively manage [interest rate risk](../Analysis%20of%20Fixed%20Income%20Securities.md),  optimize [portfolio](../../Advanced%20Investments/An%20Asset%20Allocation%20Primer.md) performance,  and navigate the complexities of [fixed income markets](../../Financial%20Engineering/A%20Practical%20Guide%20to%20Bonds%20and%20Swaps.md).

This concludes the lecture notes on [Eurodollar futures](../../Financial%20Markets/Financial%20Engineering%20and%20Arbitrage%20in%20the%20Financial%20Markets/PART%20I%20RELATIVE%20VALUE%20BUILDING%20BLOCKS/Chapter%206%20Options%20on%20Non-Price%20Variables/Convexity-Adjusted%20Models%20for%20LIBOR%20Forwards%20Qu.md),  [SOFR futures](../../Financial%20Markets/Fixed%20Income%20Securities%20Tools%20for%20Today's%20Markets/Chapter%2012/One-Month%20SOFR%20Futures.md),  [Basis Swap](A%20Guide%20to%20the%20Front%20End%20and%20[[Basis%20Swaps) Markets#Federal Funds Market|[Fed Funds](../../Financial%20Markets/Fixed%20Income%20Securities%20Tools%20for%20Today's%20Markets/Chapter%2012/Fed%20Fund%20Futures.md)]] [futures](../../Financial%20Markets/Financial%20Engineering%20and%20Arbitrage%20in%20the%20Financial%20Markets/PART%20I%20RELATIVE%20VALUE%20BUILDING%20BLOCKS/Chapter%203%20-%20Futures%20Markets/Futures%20Not%20Subject%20to%20Cash-And-Carry.md),  and advanced [interest rate futures](../../Financial%20Engineering/Derivatives/Part%20III%20-%20Fixed%20Income%20Futures%20Contracts/Chapter%2012%20-%20Hedging%20with%20Interest%20Rate%20Futures.md) contracts. Next,  we will explore practical applications of these instruments in [portfolio construction](../../Financial%20Markets/Financial%20Asset%20Pricing%20Theory%20Overview/Chapter%2012%20-%20Derivatives/Exercises.md) and [risk management](../../Financial%20Engineering/Financial%20Mathematics%20Course.md).